channel.title: Latest release question
channel.description:
Hey .)
I know a lot of changes has been done to Axoloti and I was wondering if it is still possible to download new objects without dowlnoading the software? For example I'd like ot try the sine lfo with the phase input, but cannot find it on Github.
Any ideas where to find the new objects?
Thanks

item.title: Latest release question
item.dc:creator: @johannes johannes
item.description:
@johannes wrote:

They're upwards version compatible, not downwards version compatible.
A 1.0.8 version object won't load in 1.0.6.

Read full topic

item.title: Latest release question
item.dc:creator: @thetechnobear Mark Harris
item.description:
@thetechnobear wrote:

NO - objects are versions to a particular release.

so you need 1.0.8 for this change... or wait for the proper release
